metadata.name: Katherine Johnson
metadata.description: Hailing from White Sulfer Springs in Greenbrier County, Katherine Johnson (August 26, 1918 - February 24, 2020) is a revered mathematician whose contributions as a "computer" for the National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) helped put a man on the moon. This token is an original hand-crafted digital sculpture created by Jamie Lester.
